data.title: Melbourne Flights, expanding its operations to 6 continents
data.meta_description:
London, 4 March 2024: Turkish Airlines, the airline flying to more countries than any other, has landed in Melbourne, marking its first destination in Australia. 

The new gateway supports the airline’s ever-expanding flight network, which now stands at 346 destinations, across six continents.
